Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of case studies in empirical software engineering research, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The focus on understanding the behaviour of software engineers in an industrial setting suggests a potential fit with the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The exploration of new research variables and the refinement of the case study design may also align with the cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of waste of resources and time in case study design suggests a potential fit with the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
